(70,'WeimB B',28,'B',3,102,296,'2 Masses, 1 Kyrie-Gloria pair, 3 Kyries, 1 Gloria, 13 Mass Proper sections, 3 Magnificats, 1 Te Deum, 1 canticle, 4 office hymns, 1 processional hymn, 3 Passions (2 in German; 2 incomplete), 21 motets, 1 set of responses, 3 Latin/German sacred pieces, 17 German sacred pieces = 75','http://www.diamm.ac.uk/jsp/Descriptions?op=SOURCE&sourceKey=2679',0,'Copied in Torgau, perhaps for use at Wittenberg Schlosskirche (GerhW). Taken from Wittenberg to Weimar by Johann Friedrich I, deposed Elector of Saxony, in 1548. Transferred to ccccc ca. 1923, but subsequently returned to Weimar.',1),
